Lubims: Lubim, apparently the same with Lehabim ([Gen
10:13](../../../bib/kjv/gen010.htm#013).md), were probably the ancient
inhabitants of Lybia (called Lubi in the Syriac version, [Act
2:10](../../../bib/kjv/act002.htm#010).md), a district of Africa, adjoining
to Egypt, and extending along the shore of the Mediterranean as far as
the city of Cyrene. [Ch2 16:8](../../../bib/kjv/ch2016.htm#008.md); [Eze
30:5](../../../bib/kjv/eze030.htm#005.md); [Nah
3:9](../../../bib/kjv/nah003.htm#009.md)

the Sukkiims: The Sukkiim (from sachach, "to cover") are supposed to
have been the Troglodites, as the LXX and Vulgate render, a people of
Egypt, on the west of the Red Sea, so called because they dwelt εν
τρωγλαις, in caves.

Ethiopians: These Cushim were probably the inhabitants of Ethiopia,
south of Egypt. [Ch2 14:12](../../../bib/kjv/ch2014.htm#012.md), [Ch2
16:8](../../../bib/kjv/ch2016.htm#008.md); [Isa
43:3](../../../bib/kjv/isa043.htm#003.md); [Dan
11:43](../../../bib/kjv/dan011.htm#043.md); [Nah
3:9](../../../bib/kjv/nah003.htm#009.md), Cushim, Heb. [Gen
10:6-8](../../../bib/kjv/gen010.htm#006.md)

